Value.value: I heard that Sir Haldorn tripped on a broken stair yesterday.
That fiend Magnus has stolen more weapons.

Value.value: There's a commoner touching me, my lord. Please get it off me.

value.0: Tall and thin, this woman regards you imperiously, twisting her fingers together as she does. Her dress is elegant but, on closer inspection, somewhat in need of a few patches.

Value.value: My quarters are too drafty. I wish someone would fix that hole in the wall.

value.0: This peasant woman looks as though she has endured much, her weathered skin demonstrating the effects of a lifetime of hardship. A few pock-marks show where she has successfully fought off disease, and her face is hollow with hunger and exhaustion.

Value.value: Gauw aweh un' lemmeh ge' aun wi' meh wurk.
Thank th' gods there beh naun on th' gallows. I' right stinks wi' summun oop thar!
Yeh're nae from araund these parts, ayup.

value.0: This peasant is thin and dirty from his work in the fields and is clearly living hand-to-mouth. His clothes are shabby and his face bears the hollow expression of a man who is hungry, anxious and worn out.

Value.value: Hauw de I knauw ye'll nae repaurt meh t' th' Knichts?
It beh mighteh cauld hehr inna winter. 'S nae guid fehr th' crops.
Daun' yeh gauw nehr ol' Cutter Fahan's place. 'E bin dead fer t'reh yehr nauw!
